<article lang="en-US"><sect1><title/><sect2><title/><sect3><title>Toolbar</title>
<para>A <code>toolbar</code> is used to place a series of buttons, such as <code>toolbarbutton </code>or <code>button. </code>The toolbar buttons could be used without toolbars, so a toolbar could be used without tool buttons. However, tool buttons change their appearance if they are placed inside a toolbar.</para>
<para>The toolbar has two orientation: <code>horizontal </code>and <code>vertical. </code>It controls how the buttons are placed.</para>
<para>See also : <olink targetdocent="Button.xml">
<code>org.zkoss.zul.Button</code>
</olink>, <olink targetdocent="">
<code>org.zkoss.zul.Toolbar</code>
</olink>
</para>
<para>
<inlinegraphic fileref="#images/toolbar.png" width="3.198inch"/>
</para>
<title/>
<programlisting>&lt;window title="Toolbar window" border="normal" width="300px"&gt;&#13;&lt;toolbar&gt;&#13;&lt;toolbarbutton label="Left" /&gt;&lt;space/&gt;&#13;&lt;toolbarbutton label="Right" image="/img/folder.gif" dir="reverse"/&gt;&#13;&lt;/toolbar&gt;&#13;&lt;toolbar orient="vertical"&gt;&#13;&lt;button label="Left" image="/img/folder.gif" width="125px"/&gt;&#13;&lt;toolbarbutton label="Right" image="/img/folder.gif" dir="reverse"/&gt;&#13;&lt;/toolbar&gt;&#13;&lt;/window&gt;&#13;</programlisting><sect4><title>Class Name</title>
